The paper deals with the problem of learning revenue-optimal multi-item auctions, which is a central topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The paper also involves learning from data, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses graphical models to capture the correlation between bidders' valuations, which is a common technique in probabilistic graphical models and Bayesian networks (cs.DS).
